CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published (backwards) in Flash Newspicture Magazine, December 13, 1937, pg. 26, reads: "All of the Lads had a Great Time at the Westinghouse Hi-Y Initiation, held in Pittsburgh, Pa., recently. Holding several broken paddles, they are shown in a chummy lineup after the ceremonies.  Russell Washington is Counsellor of this youthful organization."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of thirteen young men, including some holding broken paddles, for Westinghouse High School initiation
